I"ß<p><a href="https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/53403110"><img src="https://zenodo.org/badge/53403110.svg" alt="DOI" /></a></p>

<p>moson (micro-organism sonification) is a collection of auditory display tools for the 
sonification and audification of atomic force microscope data recordings of the micro 
organism Dunaliella salina by Richard Thompson at the University of Durhamâ€™s Department 
of Chemistry. The auditory display aspects are part of Louise Mackenzieâ€™s larger <a href="http://www.viralexperiments.co/#!viral-experiment-2/cle2">Microbial 
Sensing</a> research project.</p>

<p>The auditory displays in moson were featured in Mackenzieâ€™s <a href="http://www.lumiere-festival.com/programme/durham/the-stars-beneath-our-feet/">Stars Beneath our Feet</a> 
installation originally commissioned by Artichoke for <a href="http://www.lumiere-festival.com/durham-2015/">Lumiere Durham 2015</a>.</p>

<p>The sonification tool <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">BacteriaActivity</code> is a patch for Max/MSP. The audification tool 
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Audify</code> is a Python executable.</p>

